oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Copy print of WWI soldier Charles William Presley
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Dressed in uniform with leggings, this studio portrait photograph of Pvt. Charles William Presley was probably taken in training camp at Camp Sevier, South Carolina. Presley served in Co. B, 117th Inf. Regt., 1st Battn., 30th Div. After he filled out his draft card he volunteered through the National Guard. He served as cook. He was overseas May 11, 1918 to March 27, 1919. He was in many battles including the breaking of the Hindenburg Line. He was discharged April 13, 1919.
